<p>Is it possible to create an Extractor object that can be used such as:</p>  <pre><code>val x = 42  x match {   case GreaterThan(80) =&gt; println("5")   case GreaterThan(70) =&gt; println("4")   case GreaterThan(60) =&gt; println("3")   case GreaterThan(40) =&gt; println("2")   case _ =&gt; println("1") } </code></pre>  <p>Now I do know that it is possible with if constructs, but I feel that it clutters my code (and seems redundant to do: <code>case MyMatcher(x) if MyCreteria(x) =&gt; _</code>), and I want to avoid that.</p>